mg src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In order to have a reservation system, it'd have to be in a central location that EVERYBODY was alerted to, which would take a great deal of work by someone who really really wanted to do it.  The point of it would be something akin to what No Trespassing signs accomplish -- those who see them and respect them will pay heed.  When they're ignored, however, there's at least the right to say something.<br>
<br>
Of course, I'm not somebody who feels you have a legal right to shoot trespassers, so hopefully that's a good analogy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zhragu>Zhragu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/03 5:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=787.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Raid - Cancelled due to Esoteric Order and Allies</span><hr size=1> A reservation system won't work. Plain and simple. There is no way to enforce it, hence, SOE themselves do not approve of them regardless of what the concensus of a server believes is right. Reservation/calendar systems died when Kunark was released and epics were to be had.<br>
<br>
That being said, it really doesn't take too much time to check this board to see what people are up to. It might be a nice gesture if you do intend to blow other's plans to possibly invite some of them who posted in the thread for epic needs. Some are guildless, or some just don't have the time to just waltz into PoF on a whim and put a raid together, hence we sign up for raids like this one.<br>
<br>
I don't say you have to do the above. Most wont. People who may possibly be considerate, or respectful of others, might send an invite to those who do not have the great fortune of time and the ability of creating a mass army or a full on guild raid. Like I said, it would have been a nice gesture that would be appreciated. An ounce of kindness goes a long way. Egotistic replies aren't seen as being &quot;nice&quot; or considerate when you are trying to claim you are.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=684960" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~asmodeus1/Zhragu_sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=paladiinkoz>paladiin koz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/03 5:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=787.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear Raid</span><hr size=1> My personal feeling is that, on a server with no official reservation system, it's impossible to think that targets can be &quot;reserved&quot;.  Otherwise, I'll just go ahead and reserve Emp Crush now!  Well, you get the idea....  I believe in First in Force, even when it works against me.<br>
<br>
However, I must also state that as a raid leader of a raiding guild (Shards of Chaos) that I don't think it's all that hard to glance at this message board and respect Open Raids.  I think open raids are a great part of the community, and let those who don't want to join Uber_Guild_01 see content they probably wouldn't otherwise.  Now I can see if Open Raids were every day, 3 times a day, and blocking content.  But that's not the case.  Open raids have become exceptionally rare now, and the situation worsens with every &quot;Screw Open Raids&quot; player that comes along.  <br>
<br>
Is it breaking rules to trample open raids? Of course not.  But saying you don't respect the open raiding community to take 30 seconds to check a schedule sure speaks volumes about a guild.  Saying someone else would have tagged the target is simply an attempt at justification.  Sure there's FiF, but there's also compassion.  <br>
<br>
*Shrug* it's only a game.  But even so, it sure can be frustrating to watch as guilds just blatently don't care about others' attempts to help the FV community through open raids.  As someone who's done their share of Open Raid leading, I can feel for those who were planning to have a shot at their epic drops.  Obviously it's not the end of the world, but surely disappointing to see the actions of some guilds nowadays.<br>
<br>
I don't think it's asking much for raiders to take a moment and check for open raids, especially ones posted so far in advance.  Cmon FV'ers, we're better than this. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=747613">Kozz</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
